title: Submission Complete
message: Thank you for completing the questionnaire!

data.meaning: Your risk is lower than most women (below the 50th percentile).
data.action: Keep up with routine checkups, like yearly breast exams by a doctor from 30 years of age.

data.meaning: Your risk is average or slightly higher (50th to 75th percentile).
data.action: Consider breast exams every 6 months from 30 years of age and talk to your doctor about prevention.

data.meaning: Your risk is higher (75th to 95th percentile).
data.action: Get breast exams every 4-6 months from 25 years of age and possibly imaging (like mammograms) as advised by your doctor.

data.meaning: Your risk is very high (top 5% of women).
data.action: Be extra vigilant with breast exams every 4 months from at least 25 years of age and more frequent imaging as per your doctor's advice.

disclaimer.title: Disclaimer
disclaimer.text: This Report is intended for research purposes only. The Breast cancer risk assessment algorithm is currently under development and should not be considered clinically validated. For medically relevant decisions and clinically valid results, please consult a qualified clinician.

pdf.alertNoData: Form data is not available to generate a PDF.
